HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 98
BY REPRESENTATIVE CHASSION
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates April 8, 2026, as Big Brothers Big Sisters
Day at the state capitol
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as Big Brothers Big Sisters Day at the state capitol.
3 WHEREAS, youth served by Big Brothers Big Sisters programs experience
4 improved academic outcomes, stronger relationships, higher aspirations, and greater
5 long-term economic success; and
6 WHEREAS, Big Brothers Big Sisters of Southwest Louisiana, Big Brothers Big
7 Sisters of Acadiana, and Big Brothers Big Sisters of Greater New Orleans work to create and
8 support one-to-one mentoring relationships that ignite the power and promise of youth; and
9 WHEREAS, these organizations work to unlock the potential of Louisiana's children
10 by creating and supporting relationships between young people from age six to young
11 adulthood, who are referred to as "Littles", and caring volunteer mentors, who are referred
12 to as "Bigs"; and
13 WHEREAS, innovative initiatives such as the Big Futures program expand the
14 organization's reach through a dual-impact mentoring model in which high school students
15 serve as mentors to younger youth while receiving structured workforce-readiness
16 programming; and
17 WHEREAS, participants in Big Futures, who are referred to as "High School Bigs",
18 develop leadership skills, strengthen academic engagement, and gain exposure to financial
19 literacy, professional development, postsecondary pathway planning, and more; they also
20 model positive behaviors and academic commitment for younger students; and
