1 WHEREAS, this model not only supports the growth and success of mentees, but
2 prepares participating high school students to become engaged citizens and role models; and
3 WHEREAS, during the 2025 fiscal year reporting period, the organization served six
4 hundred eighty-five youth statewide, recruited four hundred eighty-one prospective
5 volunteers, and served four hundred new youth through expanded one-to-one relationships,
6 High School Bigs, and small-group mentoring models; and
7 WHEREAS, Big Brothers Big Sisters of Acadiana, Big Brothers Big Sisters of
8 Southwest Louisiana, and Big Brothers Big Sisters of Greater New Orleans demonstrate
9 unwavering commitment in their mission to ignite the potential of Louisiana's youth, and
10 their efforts are most deserving of the highest recognition.
11 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
12 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as Big Brothers
13 Big Sisters Day at the state capitol and does hereby express enduring appreciation for the
14 contributions made to Louisiana youth by Big Brothers Big Sisters of Acadiana, Big
15 Brothers Big Sisters of Southwest Louisiana, and Big Brothers Big Sisters of Greater New
16 Orleans.
